title: Developments in the Theory and Practice of Cybercartography, Vol
description:
English | 2014 | ISBN: 0444627138 | ISBN-13: 9780444627131 | 394 pages | PDF | 31,4 MB

Cybercartography is a new paradigm for maps and mapping in the information era. 

Defined as the organization, presentation, analysis and communication of spatially referenced information on a wide variety of topics of interest to society, cybercartography is presented in an interactive, dynamic, multisensory format with the use of multimedia and multimodal interfaces.
